<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine - Model Years Late 1997 to 2003 - Cylinder Head And Valves - Fuel
        Injector Sleeve - Cleaning Bores, Fuel Galleries and Oil Galleries
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="5">
        <title>Cleaning Bores, Fuel Galleries and Oil Galleries</title>
        <figure id="f1200451" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg2/EG2543.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Cleaning the Fuel Injector Bore</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Injector Sleeve Bottom Brush</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Injector Bore</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert the injector sleeve bottom brush into the fuel injector bore to remove deposits and
                hardened sealant from the bore.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure>
            <graphic filename="../figeg9/EG9115.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="392px"/>
            <caption>Oil Rail End Plugs</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Rail End Plug (two per cylinder head)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the two oil rail end plugs (one located at each end of the cylinder head).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert a stiff nylon brush into the oil gallery.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200452" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg2/EG2552.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Cleaning the Oil Galleries</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Small Nylon Brush In Oil Gallery Port</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Galley Port</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Injector Bore</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the three oil gallery plugs and the high pressure oil supply fitting. Insert a small
                stiff nylon brush into each oil gallery.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200453" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg2/EG2549.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Cleaning the Fuel Galleries</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Small Nylon Brush In Fuel Gallery Port</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Injector Bore</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the two fuel gallery plugs. Insert a small stiff nylon brush into each fuel
                gallery.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200454" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg2/EG2551.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Cleaning the Fuel and Oil Galleries With Compressed Air</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Gallery</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Injector Bore</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Air Nozzle</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use filtered compressed air to clean out all debris from the fuel and oil gallery ports.
            </para>
        </step1>
